00:05:26.050 --> 00:05:29.900
So times 10, and what
does that equal to?

00:05:29.900 --> 00:05:36.320
Let me get my high-end
calculator here.

00:05:36.320 --> 00:05:38.800
So let's see what that is.

00:05:38.800 --> 00:05:53.860
That is 0.8 times 0.8 times 0.8
times 0.2 times 0.2 times 10.

00:05:53.860 --> 00:05:56.450
Equals 20.48.

00:05:56.450 --> 00:06:03.980
So it's essentially, a 20.48%
chance that I get exactly

00:06:03.980 --> 00:06:06.076
3 out of 5 of the baskets.

00:06:06.076 --> 00:06:10.340
Now let's make it slightly
more interesting.

00:06:10.340 --> 00:06:12.980
Let's say I don't want it as a
probability of 3 out of the 5.

00:06:12.980 --> 00:06:15.050
And this is actually something
that probably, people

00:06:15.050 --> 00:06:16.145
are more likely to ask.

00:06:16.145 --> 00:06:19.080
 

00:06:19.080 --> 00:06:25.260
What is the probability of
getting at least 3 baskets?

00:06:25.260 --> 00:06:28.350
 

00:06:28.350 --> 00:06:30.070
Well, if you think about it,
